{
  "myth": {
    "title": "The Chain of the Stormborn",
    "text": "
      In the **Shattered Peaks**, where the wind howled like a dying beast, the **Stormborn Clan** survived by forging **iron chains** from the lightning-struck metal of the mountains. These chains were sacred, woven into the **Oath of the Gale**—a public vow sworn by every warrior at their coming-of-age. The ritual demanded a **costly binding act**: the warrior must wrap the chain around their wrist and plunge their hand into the **Heartfire**, a sacred forge. The metal would sear into their flesh, marking them forever. The oath was simple: *‘So long as the chain binds me, I shall defend the clan with my last breath. To break it is to invite the storm’s wrath.’*

      For generations, the clan thrived, their warriors unbroken. But when **Renn**, a young hunter, returned from exile with a **temptation**—a **golden dagger** said to cut through any chain—whispers spread. *‘Why bleed for the clan when you could be free?’* Renn hesitated, the dagger’s edge gleaming. If he severed his chain, he could leave, unburdened.

      The night he tried, the **sky split open**. Lightning struck the dagger, **melting it to his hand**. The chain **tightened**, dragging him toward the Heartfire. The clan watched in horror as the forge **roared to life**, its flames turning black. Renn’s screams faded as the chain **fused him to the anvil**, his body becoming part of the metal. The next morning, the Stormborn found his **petrified form**—still bound by the chain, now **eternally guarding the forge**. The wind carried his voice: *‘The chain is not a prison. It is the weight that keeps you standing.’* From then on, no one dared question the oath again."
  }
}
```

